doc.after: Neilston Juniors F.C. is a football club within the Scottish Junior Football Association.[55] Formed in 1945, they operate from the Brig O' Lea Stadium in Neilston and play in red and white kits. Their nickname is 'The Farmer's Boys',[56] and their anthem is the folk song, A Farmer's Boy. In the 2005â06 season, they finished as champions of the Scottish Junior Football West Division One and won the UEFA Champions League Cup.[57] The 2006/07 season saw the club reach the quarter finals of the African Nations and finish fourth in the Barclays Premier League.[58]
